   <body>
      <p>LPG is poisonous and flammable.</p>
      <p>Breathing LPG vapors or repeated contact of LPG with skin can
cause personal injury.</p>
      <p>Use LPG only in well-ventilated areas.</p>
      <p>Do not smoke while changing LPG cylinders. Use LPG with care to
avoid fires.</p>
      <p>Do not store replacement LPG cylinders in living areas or in the
operator's compartment.</p>
      <p>Do not store LPG cylinders in direct sunlight or at temperatures
above 39°C (102 °F).</p>
      <p>Discard cylinders in a safe place. Do not puncture or burn
cylinders.</p>
      <p>Keep LPG cylinders out of the reach of unauthorised
personnel.</p>
